<P>
Denis Doyle, Senior Fellow in Education at Heritage and author
of the study, reviews H.R. 3467, Saving Our Children:  The American
Community Renewal Act of 1996.  Title II of this provision would
implement an education choice scholarship program that includes
both private and religious schools in areas deemed to be &quot;renewal
communities.&quot; The proposed legislation would allow each locality
to determine the value of the special scholarships, with the maxiumum
value being no greater than the existing per-capita cost of education
in the local public school district. Doyle determines that this
legislation will enable poor children to enroll in better schools
and give their parents more choices concerning their education.
