<B><font size=3>Clean Air Violations May Become Easier to Prove,  
</FONT></B><font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">by
Jonathan Marte,</FONT>
<p>
<i><font size=3>Legal Backgrounder</font>
<p></i>
Martel analyzes the dramatic change in the evidence required to prove a violation of the Clean Air 
Acts emissions limit. This paper also examines EPAs CAM rulemaking and a recent court decision 
