<Hr>
<B>The Atlantic Institute for Market Studies Presents:
<I><B>The Coming Revolution in <BR>
Local Government </B></I></B>
<P>
Nova Scotia, Canada: March 28-29
<P>
This is a conference on making
downsizing a success for local governments and their taxpayers.
Participants will examine the idea that local government everywhere
is undergoing revolutionary change. Presenters will offer overviews
of Canadian and international cases of downsizing, give advice
about contracting out and privatization, ensuring service quality
and the legal obligations of local governments under such arrangements.
In addition, it will be explained how municipalities can perform
&quot;opportunity audits&quot; to identify areas in which these
innovations can be put to work today. This approach will be contrasted
with administrative changes such as amalgamation and fashionable
ideas like &quot;public-private partnerships.&quot; CONTACT: Lynne
Pascoe, Director of Development, Atlantic Institute for Market
Studies, 1326 Barrington Street, Halifax, NS B3J 1Z1, 902/429-1143.
<BR>

