<head>
<title>LI-Youth Leadership School Information</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<!-- <img align=right alt="drawing of graduates" hspace=8 vspace=20 src="yli1.gif">-->
<img src="sc-logo.gif"><p>
<h4>The Leadership Institute has trained thousands of young conservatives to be successful in politics.
<p>

<h2>Youth Leadership School</h2>
<B><a href="rg-sc-yl.html">Register Now </A></B><BR>
</center><pre><b>
			Lincoln, NE 	- January 20-21, 1996
			Provo, UT 	- January 26-27
			Atlanta, GA 	- February 3-4
			Denver, CO 	- February 3-4
			St. Louis, MO 	- February 10-11
			Dallas, TX 	- February 10-11
			Madison, WI 	- February 17-18
			Orlando, FL 	- February 17-18
			Philadelphia, PA- February 24-25
			Boston, MA 	- February 24-25
			Seattle, WA 	- March 2-3
			Bob Jones U, SC - March 8-9
			Ann Arbor, MI 	- March 23-24
			Baton Rouge, LA - April 13-14
			Chapel Hill, NC - April 13-14
			Richmond, VA 	- April 20-21
			Houston, TX 	- April 20-21 
			Washington, DC	- June 15-16
			Washington, DC  - July 27-28
			San Diego, CA	- August 17-18
<br></b></pre>  
<p>
Morton Blackwell's Youth Leadership School is the only program of its kind.  Its your opportunity to learn to organize large numbers of young people for the candidates and causes of their choice.  Each year the Youth Leadership School starts the career of many young conservatives in the public policy process.
<p>
The Leadership Institute's nationwide reputation for providing well-trained talent creates a high demand for its graduates.  <b>Youth Leadership School graduates are highly sought after for their political expertise and leadership abilities.</b>
<p>
At the Youth Leadership School, you'll learn how to:<br>
<ul>
<b><li>Activate and lead students for the candidates of your choice
<li>Recruit hundreds of new members for your club or organization
<li>Convince the news media to present your side of the issues</b>
</ul>
Upon graduation from the Youth Leadership School, you'll have the skills required to succeed in politics.
<p>
<center>
<b>For more information call 1-800-827-LEAD or fax (703) 321-6034</b>
<p>
<Font Size="-1">The Leadership Institute is a 501(c)(3) non-profit, non-partisan educational foundation.<br>
It does not support, endorse or oppose candidates or proposed legislation.</Font Size>
<p>
<p>
</center>
<p>
