<head>
<title>Student Publications School</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="sc-logo.gif"><p>
<h3>Student Publications School</h3>
<p></center>
Feeling censored on your campus?<br>
Want to have your views heard?

<p>
<b>You can beat speech codes, multiculturalism and political correctness.  The Leadership Institute Student Publication School will show you how.</b><br>
Challenge the liberal news monopoly.
Over 1000 students have attended the Student Publications School.  LI is responsible for training staff members on over 60% of conservative campus newspapers.
<p>
<blockquote>
<i><center>"There is nothing like this elsewhere under one roof and available with scholarship.  Saves hundreds of hours of trial and error and many examples of outright failure."<br></i>
-- David Linton, Columbia University / SPS 1994
<p>
<i>"The SPS has done the best job of educating me - in only 48 hours - to start a school newspaper.  SPS has helped me more than anyone, and I value all I have learned."<br></i>
-- Kevin Clark, Nebraska Wesleyan / SPS 1993
</i></center>
</blockquote><p>
<b>Start your own independent, conservative campus newspaper.</b><br>
The Leadership Institute's Student Publications School teaches you the "nuts and bolts" of how to start and fund a paper or improve an existing one.  Learn from expert faculty, including some of the best conservative fund raisers and journalists in the country.
<p>
<b>
Learn how to:
<ul>
<li>Gain donor and foundation support
<li>Devise a successful advertising strategy
<li>Develop an effective editorial policy
<li>Create attractive layout
<li>Deal with complicated legal issues
</ul></b>
<p>
[ <a href="home.html">Home</a> | <a href="mailto:schools@townhall.com">E-mail</a> ]
<p><center><font size="-1">The Leadership Institute is a 501(c)(3) non-profit, non-partisan educational foundation.<br> It does not support, endorse or oppose candidates or proposed legislation.<br> All contributions to the Leadership Institute are tax deductible.<br></font></center></body>
