<head>
<title>LI-Public Relations School</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="sc-logo.gif">
<p>
<h2>Public Relations School</h2>
<center><b>Internet Applicants receive $25 discount on registration</b></center>
</center>
<pre><b>
			1996

			Washington, DC	- November 19-20

			1997

			Washington, DC - February 6-7
			Washington, DC - April 10-11
			Washington, DC - July 10-11
			Washington, DC - November 17-20 (Evenings)
</b></pre><p>
Want to get your message through the hostile media environment?  Many political battles are won or lost in newspapers and broadcast media coverage.  To win, you must be able to deal effectively with the media.
<p>
The Leadership Institute's Public Relations School will teach you how to use the liberal media to your advantage.   You'll learn to:
<ul>
<li>Develop an effective media strategy
<li>Frame Issues in your favor
<li>Set up a successful media event
<li>Hold a good press conference</ul>
<p>
You'll learn from the top-notch faculty which includes:
<ul>
<li>Former White House press secretaries
<li>Seasoned political pros
<li>Famous media consultants
<li>Public relations professionals</ul>
<p>
<center>
<b>For more information contact Brian Scully at 1-800-827-LEAD or fax (703) 247-2001</b>
