<p>
<h3>Student Publications School</h3><p>
<b>Feeling censored on your campus?<br>
Want to have your views heard?<br>
Learn how to start your own conservative campus publication.
<br>Our two-day Student Publications School will give you the training you need.</b></Font Size=4>
<p>
<center><b>Internet Applicants receive $25 discount on registration</b></center>
<p>
</center>
<pre>
		<B>1996</B>
<p>
		<b>Washington, DC	- October 26-27</b></pre>
<p>
<pre>
		<B>1997</B>
<p>
		<b>Arlington, VA - February 22-23</b>
		<b>Arlington, VA - April 5-6</b>
		<b>Arlington, VA - July 12-13</b>
		<b>Arlington, VA - September 27-28</b>
		<b>Arlington, VA - November 8-9</b>
</pre>
<p>
<b>
Learn how to:
<ul>
<li>Gain donor and foundation support
<li>Devise a successful advertising strategy
<li>Develop an effective editorial policy
<li>Create attractive layout
<li>Deal with complicated legal issues
</ul></b>
<p>

<b>Start your own independent, conservative campus newspaper.</b><br>
The Leadership Institute's Student Publications School teaches you the nuts and bolts of how to start and fund a paper or improve an existing one.  Learn from expert faculty, including some of the best conservative fund-raisers and journalists in the country.
<p>
<b>You can beat speech codes, multiculturalism and political correctness!</b><br
>
Challenge the liberal campus news monopoly. Over 700 students have attended the Student Publications School in recent years. LI is responsible for training staff members on over 60% of conservative campus newspapers.
<p>

<center><b>For more information call David Gersten at 1-800-827-LEAD or Fax (703) 247-2001</b><p>
</center>

