<html>
<head>
<title>The Laws Of The Public Policy Process</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="/lead-inst/li-logo.gif"><br>
<h3>The Laws Of The Public Policy Process</h3>
</center>
<ol><small>
<li> Never give a bureaucrat a chance to say no.
<LI> Don't fire all your ammunition at once.
<LI>  Don't get mad except on purpose. 
<LI> Effort is admirable. Achievement is valuable. 
<LI> Make the steal more expensive than it's worth. 
<LI> Give 'em a title and get 'em involved.
<LI>  Expand the leadership. You can't beat a plan with no plan.
<LI>  Political technology determines political success.
<LI>  Sound doctrine is sound politics. 
<LI> In politics, you have your word and your friends; go back on either and you're dead. 
<LI> Keep your eye on the main chance and don't stop to kick every barking dog. 
<LI> Don't make the perfect the enemy of the good.
<LI>  Remember the other side has trouble too. 
<LI> Don't treat good guys like you treat bad guys.
<LI>  A well-run movement takes care of its own. 
<LI> Hire at least as many to the right of you as to the left of you.
<LI>  You can't save the world if you can't pay the rent. 
<LI> All gains are incremental; some increments aren't gains.
<LI>  A stable movement requires a healthy, reciprocal I.O.U. flow among its participants. Don't keep a careful tally.
<LI>  An ounce of loyalty is worth a pound of cleverness. 
<LI> Never miss a political meeting if you think there's the slightest chance you'll wish you'd been there. 
<LI> In volunteer politics, a builder can build faster than a destroyer can destroy. 
<LI> Actions have consequences. 
<LI> The mind can absorb no more than the seat can endure. 
<LI> Personnel is policy. 
<LI> Remember it's a long ball game. 
<LI> The test of moral ideas is moral results.
<LI>  You can't beat somebody with nobody. 
<LI> Better a snake in the grass than a viper in your bosom. 
<LI> Don't fully trust anyone until he has stuck with a good cause which he saw was losing.
<LI>  A prompt, generous letter of thanks can seal a commitment which otherwise might disappear when the going gets rough. 
<LI> Governing is campaigning by different means. 
<LI> You cannot make friends of your enemies by making enemies of your friends.
<LI>  Choose your enemies as carefully as you choose your friends. 
<LI> Keep a secure home base. 
<LI> Don't rely on being given anything you don't ask for. 
<LI> In politics, nothing moves unless it's pushed.
<LI>  Winners aren't perfect. They made fewer mistakes than their rivals.
<LI>  One big reason is better than many little reasons. 
<LI> In moments of crisis, the initiative passes to those who are best prepared. 
<LI> Politics is of the heart as well as of the mind. 
Many people don't care how much you know until they know how much you care. 
<LI> Promptly report your action to the one who requested it. 
<LI> Moral outrage is the most powerful motivating force in politics.
<LI>  Pray as if it all depended on God; work as if it all depended on you.
</small></ol>

<P>
