<head>
<title>Participate in the Leadership Institute's Charitable Gift Annuity Program</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<h2>Participate in the Leadership Institute's Charitable Gift Annuity Program</h2>
<h4>Receive an income for life. Strengthen the Institute's programs. Realize significant tax savings.</h4>
</center>
 A Leadership Institute Gift Annuity is an agreement which provides incorne for life in exchange for a gift of cash or securities to the Institute.<p>

The principal amount of the gift, the age of the annuitant at the tine of the gift and the I.R.S. discount rate are wed to determine the fixed amount of income paid the annuitant.<p>

The Leadership Institute invests 70% of the annuity gift and puts the rernaining 30% to immediate use
recruiting, training and placing young conservatives as effective public policy activisls.<p>

Itemizing taxpayers receive a federal income tax deduction in the year the gift is made. Then, for several yeas, a portion of the annuity payment can be tax-free as a return of principal.<p>

Several gift annuity options are avaliable, including:<p>

<ul>
<li>Gifls of-appreciated securities (special capital gains tax savings may apply).

<li>Two-life joint gift annuities, which provide the same fixed payment while both husband and wife are alive and then continue to the surviving spouse.

<li>Deferred payments, timed to meet college, retirement or other personal needs
</ul>

As in all legal, tax and financial malters Ihe Leadership Institute suggests potential annuitants consult with their own advisors.<p>

By law, due to imnediate tax-benefits to the donor, Leadership Institute Gift Annuities are irrevocable.<p>

For further inforrrnation on the Leadership Institute Gift Annuity Prograrn contact Mark Madsen, Director of Development at 1 (800) 827-LEAD.<p><p>
