<title>Publisher's Note
</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<h2>Publisher's Note</h2>
</center>

This issue of <i>Building Leadership</i> was once again directed by Leadership Institute intern, Liz Thornhill, of Wisner, Louisiana.<p>

Liz's internship ended in rnid-May, and the project was completed by summer intern Brian Ellis of Seattle, Washingtn. Liz wrote three articles and designed most of the layout Brian' duties were to write the staff profile on Patrick Mooney, lay out the center pages, and oversee overall production and mailing.<p>

Liz gained valuable publishing experience working on the newsletters, which will improve her skills for college and aflerward in the public policy process.<p>

As a semor at the University of Washington in Seattle, Brian is double majoring in political science and international business.  He is a graduate of the Leadership Institute's Youth Leaderhip School in May, 1994, and now enjoys working in the Finance Department of the Institute.<p>

Each year, through the generous support of its donors, the Leadership Institute hosts young conservatives to work at the Institute to get valuable office experience, perform important tasks for the Institute, and receive vital training at the Leadership Institute's schools.<p><p>

