<html>
<head>
<title>About Capital Letters</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<img src="/abic/images/capcry.gif" ALT="Capital Crying" align="left">
<p>
<center>
<hr>
<img src="/abic/images/letters.gif" ALT="CAPITAL LETTERS">
<br>
<B>America's Political Advice Column</b>
</center>
<hr>
<p>
Dear Readers:
<p>
Welcome to Capital Letters!  Take Dear Abby, Ann Landers, Hints from Heloise and Capital Gang, roll them all into one and what do you have?  <b>CAPITAL LETTERS</b>: an advice column for the politically interested but inexperienced and organizationally challenged.  Send us your political questions, queries, ideas via <a href="/abic/cl-emailer.html">e-mail</a> and we'll pick the two or three each week to answer on-line.  
<p>
Maybe you'd love to know:
<ul>
<li>how to get your congressman to pay more attention to your views;
<li>how to take control of your local school board;
<li>how to organize your neighbors into a political force on a specific cause or issue;
<li>how to find out more about your Senator's activities in Washington--things he or she 	   might not want you to know;
<li>how to get started running for office;
<li>how to build a fire under your local media and change the political climate of your area
</ul><p>
We welcome the questions -- and we'll do our best to sift through and answer the ones that have the most universal application (or are the most interesting).
<p>
Look for new letters every Monday -- and if we receive enough, we'll change them more often.
<p>
The goal?  To help put the American people back in charge of their government at every level.  We will do our best to give you the information and the tools to help you do exactly that.
<p>
<p align="right">--<a href="/abic/cdmbio.html.cgi">Cleta Mitchell</a><br>
</align>
<p>





</body></html>
