   <img src="images/title.gif">

</center>

<P>

<hr noshade>

<P>

This section is an index for the Golden State Papers Series.  This is a collection of 
policy papers published by the <B>Claremont Institute</B>, beginning in 1989, and covering a range of topics affecting law and policy in California, such as education, welfare, civll rights, privitization of public utilities, and much more.
<P>

<ul>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp53.htm"><B>GSP #53 -- The Cost of Race and Gender Preferences in California Government Contracting</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp52.htm"><B>GSP #52 -- Still Choosing by Color:</B></A> A Critique of the U.S. Department of Education Office for Civil Rights Investigation of Undergraduate Admissions at UC Berkeley

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp51.htm"><B>GSP #51 -- California's Fiscal Condition</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp50.htm"><B>GSP #50 -- The Rocky Road to Electricity Deregulation</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp49.htm"><B>GSP #49 -- The Decline of Academic Standards in California Public Education</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp48.htm"><B>GSP #48 -- Restoring School Board Options on 
Contracting Out</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp47.htm"><B>GSP #47 -- Goals 2000 and California Education:  Devolution in Retreat?</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp46.htm"><B>GSP #46 -- Unfunded Federal Mandates in Transportation:</B></A> The Case for Unilateral Devolution

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp45.htm"><B>GSP #45 -- Choosing By Color:</B></A> Affirmative Action at the University of California

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp44.htm"><B>GSP #44 -- Two Approaches to Compensated Takings Under 
the California Endangered Species Act</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp43.htm"><B>GSP #43 -- A Citizens' Guide to the State Budget Mess</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp42.htm"><B>GSP #42 -- Public Employee Compensation in California</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp41.htm"><B>GSP #41 -- Contract With California:</B></A> Charting a New Course for California Government

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp40.htm"><B>GSP #40 -- The Endangered Species Act Reconsidered</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp39.htm"><B>GSP #39 -- California's Constitution Revision Commission: Returning to the Fundamentals?</B></A>

<LI>
<A HREF="gsp38.htm"><B>GSP #38 -- The California Civil Rights Initiative: Restoring a Colorblind Constitution</B></A>

<LI>
